```python
def abbrev_num(x):
    if x == 0:
        return "0"
    
    # Handle negative numbers
    if x < 0:
        return "-" + abbrev_num(abs(x))
    
    # Convert to integer
    n = int(x)
    
    # Determine the order of magnitude
    if n < 1000:
        return str(n)
    elif n < 1000000:
        return f"{n // 1000}K"
    elif n < 1000000000:
        return f"{n // 1000000}M"
    elif n < 1000000000000:
        return f"{n // 1000000000}B"
    else:
        return f"{n // 1000000000000}T"
``` [end of text]


